<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8c52e7b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8150"><num value="8150">§ 8150.</num><heading> Effect on other statutes</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idb8c52e7c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8150/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> This subchapter does not affect the maritime rights and remedies of a master or member of the crew of a vessel.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idb8c52e7d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s8150/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s8141">Section 8141 of this title</ref> and <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s9491">section 9491 of title 10</ref> do not confer military or veteran status on any individual.</content>
</subsection>
